Mohamed Abdi Faray and Abdirahman Mohamed Isaq confessed to the crime after kidnapping the young girl in Bosaso city earlier this year. In recent months there has been an increase in the number of such attacks across Somalia. The police are currently investigating several cases, including one of a 19-year-old who was gang-raped and thrown off a six-storey building in Somalia's capital Mogadishu in September. --BBC-- 